# RULE 05 — ARCHITECTURAL DESIGN IS LAW

The file `docs/specs/IH35_ARCHITECTURAL_DESIGN.md` is the canonical reference for what every module contains.

It enumerates every module, every tab, what each tab does, what actions exist, and which Phase ships which tab.

## Before writing any UI work

1. Open the architectural design
2. Find the relevant module section
3. List every tab the module is supposed to have
4. Compare against current implementation
5. If tabs are missing, EITHER:
   - Add ALL missing tabs in this block, OR
   - Explicitly defer specific tabs by name with a tracker entry that names the future block that will add them

## Forbidden patterns

You may NEVER:
- Ship a module with FEWER tabs than the architectural design calls for, unless Jorge has explicitly approved the deferral with a tracker entry naming the missing tab AND the future block that will add it
- Add a tab to code that is NOT in the architectural design (this is drift in the other direction — equally forbidden)
- Rename a tab without updating the architectural design in the same commit

## When you discover a mismatch

If you discover a tab in code that is NOT in the architectural design:
- STOP
- Ask Jorge whether to add it to the design or remove it from code
- Do not proceed with implementation until resolved

If you discover the architectural design calls for a tab that is NOT in code AND your block is touching that module:
- Add the tab in your current block, OR
- Explicitly defer it by adding a tracker entry to `docs/trackers/phase-3.md` (or relevant phase) naming the future block that will add it

## Enforcement layer 1 — CI gate

`npm run verify:arch-design` parses the architectural design, scans the frontend for sub-nav tab counts per module, and FAILS the build if any module's actual tab count diverges from the design.

This script runs on every push to main and every PR, via `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.

## Enforcement layer 2 — PR template

`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` requires the author to confirm they reviewed the architectural design. Unchecked boxes block merge.

## Enforcement layer 3 — Pre-commit hook

`.husky/pre-commit` reminds when frontend module files change but `IH35_ARCHITECTURAL_DESIGN.md` is not in the same commit. The reminder can be bypassed only with `git commit --no-verify` for cases where tab count is genuinely unchanged.

## Why this rule exists

Adding tabs without updating the design = drift = the patch-on-patch problem the previous system died from. This rule + the three enforcement layers make drift impossible to ship undetected.
